  "text": "Similar to the work by Gavrila and Giebel [CITATION_1] , templates for matching are divided into several hierarchy levels in order to accelerate matching. In the matching procedure, we tracking performance particles time bad 10 0.2344s reasonable 50 1.0469s good 100 2.1095s Table 1 . The trade-off between the number of particles and tracking performance. The time indicated is the required time (in Matlab) to track a person whose size is 70 × 220 pixels. Bad, reasonable and good tracking performance corresponds with loss of tracking of 77%, 22% and 8% during occlusion, respectively.",
